# Spring Boot Repository Patterns

## 📌 PURPOSE

Repository layer handles database operations.

---

## 🧱 STRUCTURE

### DO

* Use Spring Data JPA
* Extend `JpaRepository`

### EXAMPLE

```java
@Repository
public interface TaskRepository extends JpaRepository<Task, Long> {
}
```

---

## ⚙️ RESPONSIBILITIES

### DO

* Perform CRUD operations
* Query database

---

## 🔍 CUSTOM QUERIES

### DO

* Use method naming:

```java
findByStatus(String status)
```

---

## 🚫 DO NOT RULES

* No business logic
* No DTO usage
* No validation logic

---

## ⚙️ BEST PRACTICES

### DO

* Keep repository simple
* Use JPA conventions

---

## 🧪 TESTING

### DO

* Use integration tests for repository

---

## 🧠 AI ENFORCEMENT RULES

* MUST only handle persistence
* MUST NOT include business logic
* MUST use JPA

---

